  "translations": {
    "en": {
      "description": {
        "text": "In the woods by the Rud district of Karlstad, there are several crags and scattered boulders. Mainly problems in the easier grades, but there are some other gems too.",
        "method": "llm",
        "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
        "sourceIds": [
          "legacy:hastsparet"
        ]
      },
      "sections": {
        "allmant": {
          "title": {
            "text": "General",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:hastsparet"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "In the woods by the Rud district of Karlstad are several crags and scattered boulders. Mainly easier problems, but there is some other good stuff too.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:hastsparet"
            ]
          }
        },
        "vagbeskrivning": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Directions",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:hastsparet"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Park by the residential area near Horsensgatan. Note that parking charges apply. Parking is prohibited at the preschool on the left if approaching from the city centre and driving up Horsensgatan. So far, there have been no issues parking in the gravel area behind the bus stop immediately after the preschool. At the very top of Horsensgatan, there is a parking bay on the left, for lazybones who drive to the floodlit running trail. Parking here makes the walk a little longer.\n\nWalk straight into the woods behind/past the preschool along one of the many well-trodden paths. You will soon reach a floodlit trail. Follow it to the left for no more than 100m or so, until you see an orange spray-painted spruce/pine beside a lamp post. Turn onto the path by the spray-painted tree. Follow this well-trodden path gently uphill over roots and rocks, passing more orange-painted trees. After about a hundred metres, you will reach a wider gravel track, Hästspåret. Follow it uphill to the left. The crags begin where the uphill section ends. The best climbing is at the bottom of the downhill section.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:hastsparet"
            ]
          }
        },
        "topo": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Topo",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:hastsparet"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Vertical wall. Problems 1–12",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:hastsparet"
            ]
          }
        },
        "problem": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Problems",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:hastsparet"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:hastsparet"
            ]
          }
        }
      },
      "routes": {
        "hastsparet-problem-3": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Use the edges to reach the top.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:hastsparet"
            ]
          }
        },
        "hastsparet-problem-5": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Take the jug and go straight up.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:hastsparet"
            ]
          }
        },
        "hastsparet-problem-7": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Straight up the face beside the crack, with a slightly scary top-out.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:hastsparet"
            ]
          }
        },
        "hastsparet-problem-8": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Start where the horizontal crack meets a vertical crack. Go straight up the face via the shallow one-finger pocket (which actually takes two fingertips). Pinch hard and go straight up to poor crimps, rearrange your feet and continue straight up via a crimp and the edge. The FA was done without the rounded Gaston hold at one o’clock, which makes it slightly easier. Variations are therefore possible. Either way, a delicate, balancy problem. The grade is uncertain. Try it and judge for yourself.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:hastsparet"
            ]
          }
        },
        "hastsparet-problem-9": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Crimp your way up to the horizontal crack.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:hastsparet"
            ]
          }
        },
        "hastsparet-problem-10": {
          "description": {
            "text": "As for the route mentioned above.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:hastsparet"
            ]
          }
        },
        "hastsparet-problem-13": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Lying start with your legs in the cave, then straight up on good holds to the ledge, where the mantle begins. A fun, unusual and excellent problem.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:hastsparet"
            ]
          }
        },
        "hastsparet-problem-14": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Same start, but make a low traverse out to the right-hand corner and then go up. An impressive squeeze on the crimp and body strength are likely to be the key ingredients.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:hastsparet"
            ]
          }
        },
        "hastsparet-problem-15": {
          "description": {
            "text": "As for Projekt in problem 14, but make the traverse high rather than low.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:hastsparet"
            ]
          }
        },
        "hastsparet-problem-16": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Sit start using the sidepull, then up.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:hastsparet"
            ]
          }
        },
        "hastsparet-problem-19": {
          "description": {
            "text": "A balance exercise left of Träben. There are obvious footholds at the far left of the boulder. Straight up, with your hands behind your back.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:hastsparet"
            ]
          }
        },
        "hastsparet-problem-20": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Sit start in the pit/hole. Previously the hardest 6b in the area if you were over 175cm tall. Original solution: left heel hook, pull your right leg out of the pit and go straight up the “arete”. New solution: right heel hook and up.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:hastsparet"
            ]
          }
        },
        "hastsparet-problem-21": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Start in the middle of the boulder and climb up via crimps.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:hastsparet"
            ]
          }
        },
        "hastsparet-problem-22": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Start in the lower horizontal crack, climb to an edge and continue via the crack trending diagonally up left. The edge has since broken off. It is unclear how this has affected the grade.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:hastsparet"
            ]
          }
        },
        "hastsparet-problem-23": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Sit start on the obvious, positive starting holds in the lower right-hand corner of the boulder. Find your way up via the arete to the lip, then follow the lip left for one metre until you reach the very, very thin vertical crack. Top out straight above it. The stone at the bottom belongs to another boulder and is, of course, out. An excellent problem offering interesting and athletic climbing. The name was taken from the project name for the first ascensionist’s then-unborn child.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:hastsparet"
            ]
          }
        },
        "hastsparet-problem-24": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Previously graded 6c.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:hastsparet"
            ]
          }
        },
        "hastsparet-problem-25": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Climb to the sidepull, then to the pinch and finish on a sloper.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:hastsparet"
            ]
          }
        },
        "hastsparet-problem-26": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Climb up along the crack.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:hastsparet"
            ]
          }
        },
        "hastsparet-problem-27": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Stand on the large stone and climb up without using the left-hand crack of route 23.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:hastsparet"
            ]
          }
        },
        "hastsparet-problem-28": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Climb on edges that just get better and better.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:hastsparet"
            ]
          }
        },
        "hastsparet-problem-29": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Start on two sidepulls, then climb up. Perhaps 6a or 6b.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:hastsparet"
            ]
          }
        },
        "hastsparet-problem-34": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Sit start up the arete.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:hastsparet"
            ]
          }
        },
        "hastsparet-problem-37": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Traverse with your hands along the sloping edge.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:hastsparet"
            ]
          }
        },
        "hastsparet-problem-38": {
          "description": {
            "text": "The face left of no. 29.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:hastsparet"
            ]
          }
        },
        "hastsparet-problem-39": {
          "description": {
            "text": "A pleasant sit start as for no. 36, then continue right and finish up 35A.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:hastsparet"
            ]
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
